summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions and statements on Sudan and South Sudan, recognizes the current situation in Abyei and along their border continues to threaten international peace and security. 
1. Decides to extend until 15 November 2019 UNISFA's mandate modification set forth in resolution 2024 (2011) and paragraph 1 of resolution 2075 (2012);
2. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
